cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with defending against backdoored neural networks, which is a security issue in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves retraining neural networks, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses CycleGAN, which is a type of generative model used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a likely category. Finally, the paper involves detecting and quarantining backdoored test inputs, which can be considered a form of anomaly detection, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
